message: "Please cite this book using the metadata in this file."
title: "Engineering Intelligence: A Quantitative Framework for Measuring, Understanding, and Optimizing Modern Software Engineering"
type: book
authors:
  - family-names: Collins
    given-names: Chris
repository-code: "https://github.com/geekychris/-Engineering-Intelligence"
url: "https://github.com/geekychris/-Engineering-Intelligence"
version: 0.1.0
abstract: >-
  Engineering Intelligence presents a quantitative framework for measuring,
  understanding, and improving modern software engineering as a socio-technical
  and economic system. It integrates engineering economics, human attention,
  architecture, delivery performance, causal inference, AI-assisted development,
  governance, instrumentation, portfolio decision-making, and organizational
  learning.
keywords:
  - software engineering
  - engineering productivity
  - developer experience
  - engineering economics
  - causal inference
  - software delivery
  - artificial intelligence
  - engineering metrics
  - socio-technical systems
  - organizational learning
